summary: The document is an FBI record pertaining to the JFK Assassination System, detailing crime conditions in Minnesota, North Dakota, and South Dakota with a focus on anti-racketeering. It includes information about the originator, date, subjects, classification, and references to investigative periods, informants, and enclosures related to the case. The document was released with deletions, last reviewed on 02/27/98, and is classified as 'UNCLASSIFIED' under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Collection.
